<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,303,379,405]" box="[189,303,379,405]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,379,405]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,379,405]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,1399,425,522]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
This species shows a North African distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Bosmans R." box="[767,947,425,452]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="85 - 103" refId="ref10330" refString="Bosmans R. 1986. Etudes sur les Linyphiidae Nord-Africaines IV. Le genre Centromerus Dahl (Araneae: Linyphiidae.). Biologisch Jaarboek Dodonaea 54: 85 - 103." type="journal article" year="1986">Bosmans 1986</bibRefCitation>
); previously the only European record was from the island of Majorca (
<bibRefCitation author="Nentwig W. &amp; Blick T. &amp; Gloor D. &amp; Hanggi A. &amp; Kropf C." box="[568,807,460,487]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref10735" refString="Nentwig W., Blick T., Gloor D. Hanggi A. &amp; Kropf C. 2020. Spiders of Europe. Version 02.2020. Available from www. araneae. nmbe. ch [accessed 14 Feb. 2020]." type="book" year="2020">
Nentwig 
<emphasis box="[678,729,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). New data reported here are the first record of this species for 
<collectingCountry box="[323,377,496,522]" name="Italy" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Italy</collectingCountry>
and for Continental Europe.
</paragraph>
